---
import LayoutFunnel from '@/layouts/LayoutFunnel.astro';
---

<LayoutFunnel title="Fitness Revenue Architecture | Marketing by Besic">
  <!-- Hero Section -->
  <section class="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-4xl text-center">
      <div class="w-20 h-20 bg-brand/10 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center mx-auto mb-8">
        <svg class="w-10 h-10 text-brand" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
        </svg>
      </div>

      <h1 class="heading-xl mb-6">
        Still Discounting to Fill Your Calendar? There's a Better Way.
      </h1>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        You're not losing to better trainers. You're losing to better positioning. The market sees you as a commodity because your marketing makes you look like one.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Image -->
      <img src="/offer-fitness-hero.webp" alt="Fitness Revenue Architecture" class="w-full rounded-lg mb-12 object-cover max-h-[500px]" width="1200" height="500" loading="eager" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Problem Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Three Reasons You're Stuck at Commodity Pricing</h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 1: You're Perceived as a Commodity</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            Your Instagram looks like every other trainer's. Your website says the same things. Your pricing is within 10% of your competitors'. When everything looks the same, the market defaults to the cheapest option. You're competing on price because you gave them no other reason to choose you.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 2: Marketing Speaks to Demographics, Not Psychology</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            "Women 25-45 interested in fitness." That's not a target audience -- that's a census category. The clients who pay EUR 5K+ for coaching don't respond to demographic targeting. They respond to psychological positioning that speaks to their identity, not their age bracket.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
          <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-brand">Leak 3: No High-Ticket Funnel</h3>
          <p class="body-md">
            You convert through volume, not value. 50 clients at EUR 100/month or 10 clients at EUR 500/month? Same revenue, but one model gives you your life back. Without a high-ticket acquisition system, you're trapped on the volume treadmill.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Image -->
      <img src="/offer-fitness-problem.webp" alt="Fitness business positioning problem" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Solution Section -->
  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">The Premium Positioning Architecture</h2>

      <!-- Phase 1 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">1</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 1: Premium Positioning Audit</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              We diagnose exactly why prospects see you as "just another trainer." Competitive positioning analysis. Messaging audit. Price perception mapping. You'll see the gap between what you deliver and how the market perceives you -- and exactly how to close it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 2 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 mb-6 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">2</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 2: Authority Architecture</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Rebuild your online presence to command premium pricing. Neurolinguistic copy that attracts EUR 5K+ clients. Content architecture that positions you as the category authority, not a service provider. Your brand becomes the reason they pay more -- not just your results.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Phase 3 -->
      <div class="bg-bg-secondary border border-white/5 rounded-xl p-8 text-left">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
          <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-brand/10 rounded-lg flex items-center justify-center flex-shrink-0">
            <span class="text-brand font-bold">3</span>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold mb-2">Phase 3: High-Ticket Acquisition System</h3>
            <p class="body-md">
              Outbound + ads + content driving EUR 5K+ clients. Application-based enrollment that filters for commitment, not price sensitivity. You stop chasing clients. Clients start applying to work with you.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution Image -->
      <img src="/offer-fitness-solution.webp" alt="Premium Positioning Architecture system" class="w-full rounded-lg my-12 object-cover max-h-[300px]" width="1200" height="300" loading="lazy" />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Execution Gap Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-[#111111] relative z-10">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-8 text-center">Most Agencies Deliver Reports. We Deliver Revenue.</h2>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center">
        The gap between knowing you're underpriced and actually commanding premium is where fitness businesses stall for years. Your last marketing hire made your Instagram prettier. Your pricing didn't move. Our framework closes the execution gap by rebuilding your positioning, not your content calendar.
      </p>
      <p class="body-md mb-6 text-center font-semibold text-brand">
        We took a fitness coach from discount pricing to premium, tripling their average client value in 90 days.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA Section -->
  <section class="py-20 pb-48">
    <div class="container-custom max-w-3xl text-center">
      <h2 class="heading-lg mb-6">Apply for a Revenue Diagnosis</h2>
      <p class="body-lg mb-12">
        We work with fitness professionals generating EUR 100K+ annually who know they should be charging more. If that's you, apply below.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-12 flex justify-center w-full">
        <a
          href="/en/apply"
          class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-lg font-bold text-white transition-all duration-300 bg-[#8224e3] rounded-lg hover:bg-[#6a1ca6] hover:scale-105 shadow-[0_0_20px_rgba(130,36,227,0.4)]"
        >
          Apply for Revenue Diagnosis
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</LayoutFunnel>
